\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Liz and Bridget:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> After Liz and Bridget were worried about Evan's health in the previous scene, the energy improves. Bridget noticed that Sarah had been rubbing her pendant like a worry stone. Bridget inquired about Sarah's pendant. The retelling of the story how Evan had the pendant custom-made for her left Liz and Bridget in a state of bewilderment that Evan actually had the capability of doing something like that, and left them with warm hearts at the sentimentality of his gesture.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Sarah:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> Sarah was feeling more and more like a part of the family. Without any intention to do so, she became the center of attention as she relived the sentimental story about receiving Evan's special gift \endash  the pendant. She was excited to tell the story, and impacted emotionally as she relived the moment she received the gift..<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Evan:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> Evan is okay with Sarah telling the story, but he doesn't think it's a big deal. He even seems to feel a little awkward. Custom designing jewelry isn't something he's known for. He probably thinks his friends would think it's lame. But this is it really talked about in the scene. The reader can determine for themselves why Evan doesn't think it's a big deal.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Joe:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> Joe's been mostly silent for the middle part of the dinner scenes. Evan makes a joke about turning the women's focus to interrogating Joe. Joe and comical style makes an excuse that he needs to go cook the turkey. He does not want to be the focus of the women's attention.<!$Scr_Cs::2><!$Scr_Ps::5>}
