\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::6>Evan looked at Joe, sensing a good moment to lighten the mood. }
\par\plain {\f5\fs26\b1\cf10 <$Scr_Cs::7>Evan: <!$Scr_Cs::7>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 "You know, Joe, I think it's your turn to get some attention. How about we all interrogate you for a while!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Without missing a beat, Joe stood up, grinning broadly. }
\par\plain {\f5\fs26\b1\cf10 <$Scr_Cs::7>Joe: <!$Scr_Cs::7>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 "Gotta go finish carving the turkey for leftovers tomorrow!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The room erupted in laughter, effectively shifting the atmosphere back to the jovial, holiday spirit that had briefly waned.<!$Scr_Ps::6>}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 Bridget(curious)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93I noticed you rubbing that adorable little pendant. I've never seen anything like that before. Is it some kind of worry stone?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::2>Liz jumped in.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Liz:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Yes! I noticed you rubbing it earlier as well, but I didn't want you to feel like I was watching you. I'm glad you mentioned it, mom.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Sarah turned to Evan.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Sarah }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (surprised)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93You didn't tell them about my pendant?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Evan }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (hoping to slough it off)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Ah, it's no big deal.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Bridget:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, you don't have to be so embarrassed for buying your girlfriend such a cute gift as a token of your affection.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Sarah }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (piped into the conversation without thinking the check with Evan)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93He didn't exactly buy it?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Joe had been quietly listening happy that the focus was not on him, but on Evan. But he couldn't resist jumping in for some fun.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Joe }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (joking)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93What did you do, Evan? Steal it?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Sarah looked at Evan, she could see that he was embarrassed about the whole situation, but didn't understand why. She presumed it was modesty.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Sarah:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93May I share our story?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Evan looked around at his mom and sister and surmise there was no point in resistance.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Evan:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Go ahead, I'm sure I would be disowned if I said no.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::2>Sarah told the whole story. Generally, Sarah is not a very good storyteller. She tends to be a little stiff and monotone. Her students can attest to that. But when it came to talking about Evan's gift to her, her face let up her body became animated and by the end of the story her eyes watered. Sarah spent the next 25 minutes telling the story in vivid detail, while the boys are away from the table preparing for dessert. By the time there was finished all three Evan were teary-eyed. However, Liz was struggling to believe it.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 She looked at Evan.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Liz }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (expressing some doubt)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Gosh, it's so hard to believe my bratty little brother is even capable of doing something like that. Evan, did you really design that and have that custom-made? Now\u8217\'92s the time to come clean, it's a nice gift no matter what.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Joe looked at Liz like she was crazy.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Joe }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (stating a well-known fact)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93When have you ever heard Evan lie about anything unless it was to protect someone's feelings?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Liz }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (truthful, but meaning it as humor)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93I remember lots of times Evan lied. Like when he took mom\u8217\'92s car for a joy ride in the middle of the night when she was sleeping.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Bridget said nothing out loud, but gave Evan a look as if to say you did what?}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Evan }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (defending his honor, and playfully making a point)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93I was 15 years old. I've got a long list of secrets I could tell about you Liz if you want to go down that road.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz chuckled. As good a person as Liz is considered, she is not void of skeletons in her closet.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Liz }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (backtracking)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Um. You see. Well. That was actually me mom. I took the car for a joy ride.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Everyone seemed to have a laugh at Liz's attempt to backtrack. Nobody was taking any of this seriously.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Sarah:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93He definitely had a custom-made for me. I actually have the doll that he got the glasses from, and I had my pendant polished recently by the jeweler who custom-made it. It needed a good polish because I rub it so much. I guess I unconsciously use it as a source of comfort.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 Bridget:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Truly, Evan. That is a gift to be treasured.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Liz}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Who'd a thunk it? My bratty little brother is sweet as pie.\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0   }
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf10 Evan }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 (happy for segway to a different conversation)}{\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf10 :}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf12 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Who's ready for some Apple Pie?\u8221\'94}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Although everyone was pretty stuff from dinner they all agreed to a thin slice of pie to sweeten their pallet.}
